author: Nurudeen Obalola
title: Europa League: Fatai Scores As Ambrose, Onuachu Fall
text:
Eagles Euro Roundup , Headlines 
By James Agberebi: 
Super Eagles defender, Efe Ambrose, was in action for Celtic in their 3-1 away loss to Molde in a Europa League clash on Thursday night. 
Ambrose who played the full 90 minutes, was booked with eight minutes remaining in the match. 
Also on Thursday night, Kehinde Fatai (pictured) scored Sparta Prague’s first goal in their 2-2 draw at Schalke. 
In Denmark, Nigerian player, Paul Onuachu, was introduced in the 62nd minute for Martin Pusic but couldn’t prevent his side from losing 4-1 to Napoli. 
His Nigerian team-mate, David Akintola, was overlooked for selection as he was an unused substitute.
